00:12:26,400 --> 00:12:27,580
Muir: It's a million dollars!

263
00:12:27,611 --> 00:12:28,233
Rice: Is it?

264
00:12:28,233 --> 00:12:29,973
Muir: That's what a
million dollars sounds like.

265
00:12:30,440 --> 00:12:32,080
Offscreen: What do you mean it crashed?

266
00:12:32,820 --> 00:12:34,100
Offscreen: Kickstarter crashed.

267
00:12:37,520 --> 00:12:39,000
Muir: Kickstarter crashed!

268
00:12:39,390 --> 00:12:40,790
Schafer: No.

269
00:12:40,960 --> 00:12:44,780
[Offscreen yelling]

270
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:52,720
Rice: Yeah, that was definitely
one of the high points,

271
00:12:52,866 --> 00:12:56,318
where it was like, holy crap
-- This is a huge thing.

272
00:12:56,318 --> 00:12:58,476
Muir: Whoo! A million in 24 hours.

273
00:12:58,476 --> 00:13:00,853
Tim Schafer, you just made
a million dollars in 24 hours!

274
00:13:00,853 --> 00:13:03,442
What do you, what are you doing?

275
00:13:03,442 --> 00:13:05,355
Schafer: Yeah! I got to make a game.

276
00:13:05,355 --> 00:13:06,959
Newscaster: Over the last few
days, Tim Schafer from Double Fine

277
00:13:06,959 --> 00:13:10,448
took crowd funding site,
Kickstarter to fund his next game.

278
00:13:10,448 --> 00:13:12,638
Schafer: It feels like a happening.
You know what I mean?

279
00:13:12,638 --> 00:13:14,241
Like it feels like an event.

280
00:13:14,241 --> 00:13:16,401
Newscaster: They're raising money
at a clip of a thousand dollars per minute.

281
00:13:16,401 --> 00:13:17,697
It's incredible.

282
00:13:17,697 --> 00:13:19,270
Host: One question that is
on everybody's mind.

283
00:13:19,270 --> 00:13:20,660
You get the million dollars.

284
00:13:20,660 --> 00:13:22,541
Did you immediately withdraw it all?

285
00:13:22,541 --> 00:13:26,055
Put it into a vault and then dive
into it like Scrooge McDuck style?

286
00:13:26,055 --> 00:13:27,782
Schafer: Then during
Kickstarter, it made it,

287
00:13:27,782 --> 00:13:29,602
I don't know what it was,

288
00:13:29,602 --> 00:13:32,901
but it made everyone just take
that big basket of money

289
00:13:32,901 --> 00:13:34,805
and shake it out over our heads.

290
00:13:34,805 --> 00:13:38,100
It really was like the end
of "It's a Wonderful Life".

291
00:13:38,360 --> 00:13:58,760
[Music]

292
00:13:58,760 --> 00:14:00,320
Offscreen: So excited.

293
00:14:02,820 --> 00:14:04,080
Offscreen: Thumbs up?

294
00:14:04,347 --> 00:14:07,335
Man: Thumbs up, yes.

295
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:09,640
That was pretty amazing.

296
00:14:11,660 --> 00:14:15,340
I told you, adventure
games are not dead!

297
00:14:15,740 --> 00:14:17,520
The thing that I noticed was that

298
00:14:17,599 --> 00:14:19,512
it was just such a morale
boost to the whole team.

299
00:14:19,512 --> 00:14:22,040
And you know, I think it just
felt like a lot of goodwill

300
00:14:22,040 --> 00:14:25,123
and love coming towards the company
and everyone got super excited about it.

301
00:14:25,123 --> 00:14:26,944
And because it was like
this feeling of like,

302
00:14:26,944 --> 00:14:29,071
we knew those people were
there, we knew they were.

303
00:14:29,071 --> 00:14:31,199
But, because sometimes they don't
show up when you make a game.

304
00:14:31,199 --> 00:14:32,804
You know, you make
a game, you release it,

305
00:14:32,804 --> 00:14:34,768
you know, like I thought it was
going to sell a lot and it didn't.

306
00:14:34,768 --> 00:14:36,958
You're like, where are all
those people that it feels like,

307
00:14:36,958 --> 00:14:39,025
there's all this goodwill out there.

308
00:14:39,025 --> 00:14:40,352
Man #1: It's two million.

309
00:14:40,352 --> 00:14:43,189
Man #2: One of us has to stop shaving.

310
00:14:43,189 --> 00:14:47,622
Man #2: He has to shave my
scrotum if it gets to two million.

311
00:14:48,740 --> 00:14:50,840
Man #1: Only if he
agrees to do it on camera.

312
00:14:51,418 --> 00:14:54,193
Offscreen: Congratulations.

313
00:14:54,193 --> 00:14:55,797
Schafer: It had been a long
time since we had experience

314
00:14:55,797 --> 00:14:57,586
where it felt like we were the winners.

315
00:14:57,586 --> 00:15:00,537
We were at DICE and I
was walking through DICE,

316
00:15:00,537 --> 00:15:03,959
feeling like a winner,
which is really kind of like,

317
00:15:03,959 --> 00:15:05,871
not that I feel like a loser,

318
00:15:05,871 --> 00:15:11,539
but usually feel like the
alternative, alternative to money.

319
00:15:19,140 --> 00:15:21,120
I mean i'm proud of all our games

320
00:15:21,127 --> 00:15:23,377
and I wouldn't switch them
with anyone else's games,

321
00:15:23,377 --> 00:15:25,105
but usually walking in
a convention like that,

322
00:15:25,105 --> 00:15:27,233
you're talking to the, you know,
the people who made Uncharted

323
00:15:27,233 --> 00:15:29,146
and they're, they're really
nice and you're like, ah.

324
00:15:29,146 --> 00:15:30,780
Congratulations on the game.

325
00:15:30,780 --> 00:15:32,323
Did really well for you.

326
00:15:32,323 --> 00:15:34,729
And like, you don't often feel like,

327
00:15:34,729 --> 00:15:38,767
you feel like they're like the family
member who's like still living at home.

328
00:15:38,767 --> 00:15:40,217
You know, like yeah.

329
00:15:40,217 --> 00:15:41,975
They're all really nice
to us, but you know,

330
00:15:41,975 --> 00:15:44,838
we haven't, it's different when
you make a bunch of money.

331
00:15:44,838 --> 00:15:47,922
Schafer: And we raised 1.7
million dollars on Kickstarter.

332
00:15:47,922 --> 00:15:50,878
[Applause]

333
00:15:51,520 --> 00:15:52,980
Schafer: Is that auto refreshing?

334
00:15:52,980 --> 00:15:53,480
Everyone: Yes.

335
00:15:53,520 --> 00:15:54,840
Schafer: We were in the hotel room

336
00:15:54,844 --> 00:15:56,572
and I was listening on
the Skype, on the iPad

337
00:15:56,572 --> 00:15:58,207
and you just remember
like, click, click,

338
00:15:58,207 --> 00:16:02,611
aha, aha, then all of a sudden, whooo!

339
00:16:02,920 --> 00:16:04,980
Schafer: Distortion sound
as everyone lost their shit.

340
00:16:05,440 --> 00:16:07,920
And right now we're at
almost 2.5 million dollars.

341
00:16:07,999 --> 00:16:10,066
and we have six more days to go.

342
00:16:10,066 --> 00:16:11,578
Rice, Offscreen: Everything
moved really quickly

343
00:16:11,578 --> 00:16:13,243
and I actually didn't
really have a chance

344
00:16:13,243 --> 00:16:17,066
to like let everything sit in
until yesterday, when it finished.

345
00:16:17,066 --> 00:16:21,073
And I was like, finally it like hit
me and it was like, holy crap.

346
00:16:21,073 --> 00:16:24,615
We did something really crazy here.

347
00:16:25,720 --> 00:16:26,380
Schafer: 2 minutes!

348
00:16:27,010 --> 00:16:30,336
[Crowd shouting and cheering]

349
00:16:33,740 --> 00:16:35,080
So like we cleared in advance

350
00:16:35,080 --> 00:16:38,400
I'm going to shake this up and 
I'm going to spray it all over your head.

351
00:16:40,594 --> 00:16:41,554
Why is that...

352
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:42,940
Ron!

353
00:16:43,329 --> 00:16:45,309
My God, that's terrible for your teeth.

354
00:16:45,309 --> 00:16:46,020
Offscreen: Two minutes!

355
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:47,280
Two minutes.

356
00:16:47,420 --> 00:16:47,920
[Pop]

